body:
Initially I used a boolean flag (https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/7cb9367157eb42ee06bc6fa024522cc14a80138d) but following [this comment](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/28784#pullrequestreview-1720677514) it was changed to contain the cookie contents.

I agree that `g_generated_cookie == existing_cookie` can be `false` only if the cookie was somehow overwritten by some other process (i.e. not by `bitcoind`), so indeed it would be simpler to use the patches suggested above.

@luke-jr what do you think?

